definitions.definition: Ellipsis of babbitt metal or Babbitt metal ( “ a soft white alloy of variable composition used in bearings to diminish friction ” ) .
examples: Running while low on oil had galled the babbitt .

main_definition: Ellipsis of babbitt metal or Babbitt metal ( “ a soft white alloy of variable composition used in bearings to diminish friction ” ) .
